            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EChrist%20certainly%20felt%20the%20burden%20of%20a%20city%20that%20refused%20His%20grace%20(Luke%2019%3A41).%20Jerusalem%20had%20every%20opportunity%20to%20repent%2C%20having%20seen%20great%20miracles%20and%20having%20heard%20the%20Lord's%20greatest%20sermons.%20The%20knowledge%20that%20Jerusalem%20would%20finally%20reject%20and%20crucify%20Him%20caused%20Jesus%20to%20weep%20over%20a%20lost%20opportunity.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20also%20felt%20heartsick%20over%20Israel's%20rejection%20of%20the%20Gospel%3A%20%22My%20heart%20is%20filled%20with%20bitter%20sorrow%20and%20unending%20grief%20for%20my%20people%2C%20my%20Jewish%20brothers%20and%20sisters.%20I%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20be%20forever%20cursed-cut%20off%20from%20Christ!-if%20that%20would%20save%20them%22%20(Romans%209%3A2-3).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHave%20you%20ever%20thought%20that%20a%20certain%20person%20would%20surely%20repent%20after%20hearing%20a%20particular%20sermon%20or%20experiencing%20an%20especially%20painful%20situation%20in%20his%20life%2C%20and%20yet%20he%20did%20not%3F%20Intercession%20can%20arise%20from%20deferred%20hope%2C%20knowing%20that%20God%20is%20waiting%20to%20bless%2C%20but%20human%20beings%20are%20resisting.%20The%20pain%20and%20agony%20of%20watching%20others%20miss%20God's%20best%20in%20their%20lives%20should%20be%20turned%20into%20a%20continual%20prayer%20on%20their%20behalf.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EKeep%20on%20standing%20for%20your%20lost%20loved%20ones.%20As%20long%20as%20they%20are%20alive%20and%20breathing%2C%20there%20is%20still%20hope.%20Imagine%20the%20joy%20you%20will%20experience%20when%20they%20turn%20their%20lives%20over%20to%20God!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Joshua.19:1-20:9",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJoshua%2019%3A1-20%3A9%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_1%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJoshua%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Simeon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20second%20allotment%20of%20land%20went%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Simeon.%20Their%20homeland%20was%20surrounded%20by%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_2%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESimeon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20homeland%20included%20Beersheba%2C%20Sheba%2C%20Moladah%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_3%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHazar-shual%2C%20Balah%2C%20Ezem%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_4%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EEltolad%2C%20Bethul%2C%20Hormah%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_5%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EZiklag%2C%20Beth-marcaboth%2C%20Hazar-susah%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_6%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBeth-lebaoth%2C%20and%20Sharuhen%26%23x2014%3Bthirteen%20towns%20with%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_7%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20also%20included%20Ain%2C%20Rimmon%2C%20Ether%2C%20and%20Ashan%26%23x2014%3Bfour%20towns%20with%20their%20villages%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_8%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3Eincluding%20all%20the%20surrounding%20villages%20as%20far%20south%20as%20Baalath-beer%20(also%20known%20as%20Ramah%20of%20the%20Negev).%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3EThis%20was%20the%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Simeon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_9%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20allocation%20of%20land%20came%20from%20part%20of%20what%20had%20been%20given%20to%20Judah%20because%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory%20was%20too%20large%20for%20them.%20So%20the%20tribe%20of%20Simeon%20received%20an%20allocation%20within%20the%20territory%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_10%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Zebulun%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20third%20allotment%20of%20land%20went%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Zebulun.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3EThe%20boundary%20of%20Zebulun%26%23x2019%3Bs%20homeland%20started%20at%20Sarid.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_11%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20there%20it%20went%20west%2C%20going%20past%20Maralah%2C%20touching%20Dabbesheth%2C%20and%20proceeding%20to%20the%20brook%20east%20of%20Jokneam.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_12%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20other%20direction%2C%20the%20boundary%20went%20east%20from%20Sarid%20to%20the%20border%20of%20Kisloth-tabor%2C%20and%20from%20there%20to%20Daberath%20and%20up%20to%20Japhia.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_13%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20it%20continued%20east%20to%20Gath-hepher%2C%20Eth-kazin%2C%20and%20Rimmon%20and%20turned%20toward%20Neah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_14%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20northern%20boundary%20of%20Zebulun%20passed%20Hannathon%20and%20ended%20at%20the%20valley%20of%20Iphtah-el.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_15%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20towns%20in%20these%20areas%20included%20Kattath%2C%20Nahalal%2C%20Shimron%2C%20Idalah%2C%20and%20Bethlehem%26%23x2014%3Btwelve%20towns%20with%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_16%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Zebulun%20included%20these%20towns%20and%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_17%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Issachar%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20fourth%20allotment%20of%20land%20went%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Issachar.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_18%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EIts%20boundaries%20included%20the%20following%20towns%3A%20Jezreel%2C%20Kesulloth%2C%20Shunem%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_19%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EHapharaim%2C%20Shion%2C%20Anaharath%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_20%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3ERabbith%2C%20Kishion%2C%20Ebez%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_21%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ERemeth%2C%20En-gannim%2C%20En-haddah%2C%20and%20Beth-pazzez.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_22%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20boundary%20also%20touched%20Tabor%2C%20Shahazumah%2C%20and%20Beth-shemesh%2C%20ending%20at%20the%20Jordan%20River%26%23x2014%3Bsixteen%20towns%20with%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_23%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Issachar%20included%20these%20towns%20and%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_24%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Asher%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20fifth%20allotment%20of%20land%20went%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Asher.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_25%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EIts%20boundaries%20included%20these%20towns%3A%20Helkath%2C%20Hali%2C%20Beten%2C%20Acshaph%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_26%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EAllammelech%2C%20Amad%2C%20and%20Mishal.%20The%20boundary%20on%20the%20west%20touched%20Carmel%20and%20Shihor-libnath%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_27%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20it%20turned%20east%20toward%20Beth-dagon%2C%20and%20ran%20as%20far%20as%20Zebulun%20in%20the%20valley%20of%20Iphtah-el%2C%20going%20north%20to%20Beth-emek%20and%20Neiel.%20It%20then%20continued%20north%20to%20Cabul%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_28%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EAbdon%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A28%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20(see%20also%2021%3A30)%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3EEbron.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Rehob%2C%20Hammon%2C%20Kanah%2C%20and%20as%20far%20as%20Greater%20Sidon.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_29%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20boundary%20turned%20toward%20Ramah%20and%20the%20fortress%20of%20Tyre%2C%20where%20it%20turned%20toward%20Hosah%20and%20came%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A29%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20territory%20also%20included%20Mehebel%2C%20Aczib%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_30%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EUmmah%2C%20Aphek%2C%20and%20Rehob%26%23x2014%3Btwenty-two%20towns%20with%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_31%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Asher%20included%20these%20towns%20and%20their%20surrounding%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_32%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Naphtali%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sixth%20allotment%20of%20land%20went%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Naphtali.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_33%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3EIts%20boundary%20ran%20from%20Heleph%2C%20from%20the%20oak%20at%20Zaanannim%2C%20and%20extended%20across%20to%20Adami-nekeb%2C%20Jabneel%2C%20and%20as%20far%20as%20Lakkum%2C%20ending%20at%20the%20Jordan%20River.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_19_34%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20western%20boundary%20ran%20past%20Aznoth-tabor%2C%20then%20to%20Hukkok%2C%20and%20touched%20the%20border%20of%20Zebulun%20in%20the%20south%2C%20the%20border%20of%20Asher%20on%20the%20west%2C%20and%20the%20Jordan%20River%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A34%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eand%20Judah%20at%20the%20Jordan%20River.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20on